    question: "What is a gold IRA?",
    answer: "A gold IRA is a <strong>self-directed individual retirement account</strong> that holds physical precious metals (gold, silver, platinum, palladium) instead of paper assets. It offers the same tax advantages as traditional IRAs—tax-deferred growth or tax-free withdrawals (Roth)—while providing diversification into tangible assets that historically hold value during economic uncertainty."
